{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775860506617,"sessionID":"ses_2867b25baffebIQ2bO39tU5xmp","part":{"id":"prt_d7985fc81001tY3P7re4OhsZne","messageID":"msg_d7985b225001HMQwU5KKpy8ydd","sessionID":"ses_2867b25baffebIQ2bO39tU5xmp","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:14","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-010/tasks.md","content":"# AR-010: Router 会话管理 - Task Checklist\n\n> **AR ID:** AR-010  \n> **Module:** `pkg/router`  \n> **Language:** Go  \n> **Size:** M  \n> **Stage:** ST-3 completed  \n> **Depends on:** AR-003 (client-go), AR-009 (Router HTTP Core)\n\n---\n\n## Task 1: Create Session Types and Constants\n**Verifiable Output:** `pkg/router/session_types.go` with core type definitions\n\n- [ ] Create `session_types.go` file\n- [ ] Define `SessionStatus` string type with constants:\n  - `SessionStatusPending`, `SessionStatusActive`, `SessionStatusExpiring`, `SessionStatusTerminated`\n- [ ] Define `SessionInfo` struct with fields: SessionID, SandboxID, RuntimeRef, Status, CreatedAt, LastActivity, ExpiresAt, EntryPoints\n- [ ] Define `RuntimeReference` struct with fields: Kind, Name, Namespace\n- [ ] Define `SessionFilter` struct with fields: Status, RuntimeKind, Namespace, Before\n- [ ] Define `SessionConfig` struct with fields: DefaultTTL, MaxTTL, CleanupInterval, ActivityTimeout\n- [ ] Define `EndpointEntry` struct with fields: SessionID, SandboxID, Endpoint, LastUsed, Healthy\n- [ ] Add default constants: DefaultSessionTTL (30m), MaxSessionTTL (24h), DefaultCleanupInterval (5m), DefaultActivityTimeout (30m)\n- [ ] Add JSON tags and documentation comments\n- [ ] Write unit tests verifying type definitions\n\n**Verification Command:**\n```bash\ngo test ./pkg/router/... -v -run \"TestSessionTypes\" && \\\ngrep -E \"SessionStatus|SessionInfo|RuntimeReference\" pkg/router/session_types.go\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 2: Create Session Error Types\n**Verifiable Output:** `pkg/router/session_errors.go` with error definitions\n\n- [ ] Create `session_errors.go` file\n- [ ] Define `SessionError` struct with Code, Message, Cause fields\n- [ ] Implement `Error() string` method\n- [ ] Implement `Unwrap() error` method\n- [ ] Define sentinel errors:\n  - `ErrSessionNotFound` (code: SESSION_NOT_FOUND)\n  - `ErrSessionExpired` (code: SESSION_EXPIRED)\n  - `ErrRuntimeNotFound` (code: RUNTIME_NOT_FOUND)\n  - `ErrSandboxCreateFailed` (code: SANDBOX_CREATE_FAILED)\n  - `ErrInvalidSessionID` (code: INVALID_SESSION_ID)\n  - `ErrSessionConflict` (code: SESSION_CONFLICT)\n  - `ErrSessionStoreUnavailable` (code: STORE_UNAVAILABLE)\n- [ ] Write unit tests verifying error creation and unwrapping\n\n**Verification Command:**\n```bash\ngo test ./pkg/router/... -v -run \"TestSessionError\" && \\\ngrep \"ErrSessionNotFound\\|ErrSessionExpired\" pkg/router/session_errors.go\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 3: Create Session Manager Interface\n**Verifiable Output:** `pkg/router/session_manager.go` with interface definition\n\n- [ ] Create `session_manager.go` file\n- [ ] Define `SessionManager` interface with methods:\n  - `Resolve(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, runtimeRef RuntimeReference, createIfMissing bool) (*SessionInfo, error)`\n  - `Create(ctx context.Context, runtimeRef RuntimeReference) (*SessionInfo, error)`\n  - `Refresh(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error`\n  - `Terminate(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error`\n  - `Get(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*SessionInfo, error)`\n  - `ListActive(ctx context.Context, filter SessionFilter) ([]*SessionInfo, error)`\n  - `StartLifecycleManager(stopCh <-chan struct{})`\n- [ ] Define `sessionManager` struct with fields: store, k8sClient, workloadMgrAddr, httpClient, config, metrics, affinityRouter\n- [ ] Implement `NewSessionManager(store, k8sClient, config) SessionManager` constructor\n- [ ] Write unit tests for interface compliance\n\n**Verification Command:**\n```bash\ngo test ./pkg/router/... -v -run \"TestSessionManagerInterface\" && \\\ngrep -E \"type SessionManager interface|func NewSessionManager\" pkg/router/session_manager.go\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 4: Implement Session Resolution Logic\n**Verifiable Output:** SessionManager.Resolve method handles all resolution scenarios\n\n- [ ] Implement `Resolve()` method:\n  - If sessionID empty and createIfMissing=true, create new session\n  - Query session store by ID\n  - If found, update activity timestamp and return SessionInfo\n  - If not found, check if K8s resource exists via k8sClient\n  - If resource exists and createIfMissing, create new session\n  - If resource not found, return ErrRuntimeNotFound\n- [ ] Implement session validation (check expiration)\n- [ ] Add metrics recording for resolution duration and cache hits\n- [ ] Write unit tests for all resolution scenarios:\n  - Existing session found in store\n  - Session not found, K8s resource exists, create new\n  - Session not found, K8s resource not found\n  - Empty session ID with createIfMissing\n  - Expired session handling\n\n**Verification Command:**\n```bash\ngo test ./pkg/router/... -v -run \"TestSessionManager_Resolve\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 5: Implement Session Creation\n**Verifiable Output:** SessionManager.Create creates sessions via Workload Manager\n\n- [ ] Implement `Create()` method:\n  - Generate UUID v4 session ID\n  - Build Workload Manager request endpoint (`/v1/{kind}`)\n  - Call Workload Manager to create sandbox\n  - Wait for sandbox ready status (with timeout)\n  - Build SessionInfo from response\n  - Store session in session store with TTL\n  - Register session in affinity router\n  - Record metrics\n- [ ] Implement `mapKindToEndpoint()` helper\n- [ ] Implement `callWorkloadManager()` HTTP client method\n- [ ] Write unit tests with mock Workload Manager:\n  - Successful AgentRuntime session creation\n  - Successful CodeInterpreter session creation\n  - Workload Manager failure handling\n  - Sandbox timeout handling\n\n**Verification Command:**\n```bash\ngo test ./pkg/router/... -v -run \"TestSessionManager_Create\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 6: Implement Session Refresh and Get\n**Verifiable Output:** Session activity tracking works correctly\n\n- [ ] Implement `Refresh()` method:\n  - Retrieve session from store\n  - Update LastActivity timestamp\n  - Extend ExpiresAt (capped at MaxTTL from creation)\n  - Update store entry\n- [ ] Implement `Get()` method:\n  - Retrieve session by ID\n  - Check expiration status\n  - Return ErrSessionExpired if expired\n  - Return ErrSessionNotFound if not exists\n- [ ] Write unit tests:\n  - Refresh updates activity and extends expiration\n  - Refresh returns ErrSessionNotFound for missing session\n  - Refresh returns ErrSessionExpired for expired session\n  - Get returns correct SessionInfo\n  - Get returns error for expired session\n\n**Verification Command:**\n```bash\ngo test ./pkg/router/... -v -run \"TestSessionManager_Refresh|TestSessionManager_Get\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 7: Implement Session Termination\n**Verifiable Output:** Clean session cleanup with store and Workload Manager\n\n- [ ] Implement `Terminate()` method:\n  - Mark session as terminating in affinity router\n  - Delete session from store\n  - Call Workload Manager to delete sandbox\n  - Unregister from affinity router\n  - Record metrics (activeSessions.Dec())\n- [ ] Implement `ListActive()` method with filter support\n- [ ] Write unit tests:\n  - Successful termination flow\n  - Store delete failure handling\n  - Workload Manager failure handling\n  - ListActive with various filters\n\n**Verification Command:**\n```bash\ngo test ./pkg/router/... -v -run \"TestSessionManager_Terminate|TestSessionManager_ListActive\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 8: Create Session Resolver\n**Verifiable Output:** `pkg/router/session_resolver.go` with caching and fallback\n\n- [ ] Create `session_resolver.go` file\n- [ ] Define `SessionResolver` interface with methods:\n  - `GetSandboxBySession(ctx, sessionID, namespace, name, kind) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n  - `WarmCache(ctx, namespace) error`\n- [ ] Implement `sessionResolver` struct with store client and k8s client fields\n- [ ] Implement `GetSandboxBySession()`:\n  - Query session store first\n  - On cache miss, query K8s resource via client-go\n  - Cache result if found\n  - Return appropriate errors\n- [ ] Implement `WarmCache()` for preloading\n- [ ] Write unit tests:\n  - Cache hit scenario\n  - Cache miss with K8s fallback\n  - K8s resource not found\n  - Cache warming functionality\n\n**Verification Command:**\n```bash\ngo test ./pkg/router/... -v -run \"TestSessionResolver\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 9: Create Affinity Router\n**Verifiable Output:** `pkg/router/session_affinity.go` with sticky routing\n\n- [ ] Create `session_affinity.go` file\n- [ ] Define `AffinityRouter` struct with sessionIndex map and RWMutex\n- [ ] Implement `NewAffinityRouter()` constructor\n- [ ] Implement `GetEndpoint(sessionID)`:\n  - Returns EndpointEntry and found boolean\n  - Updates LastUsed timestamp\n- [ ] Implement `RegisterSession(sessionInfo)`:\n  - Adds session to index with endpoint from EntryPoints\n- [ ] Implement `UnregisterSession(sessionID)`:\n  - Removes session from index\n- [ ] Implement `HealthCheck(sessionID, healthy)`:\n  - Updates endpoint health status\n- [ ] Implement thread-safe operations with RWMutex\n- [ ] Write unit tests:\n  - Register and retrieve session\n  - Unregister removes session\n  - Concurrent access safety\n  - Health check updates status\n\n**Verification Command:**\n```bash\ngo test ./pkg/router/... -race -v -run \"TestAffinityRouter\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 10: Create Kubernetes Runtime Client\n**Verifiable Output:** `pkg/router/k8s_client.go` with client-go wrapper\n\n- [ ] Create `k8s_client.go` file\n- [ ] Define `RuntimeClient` struct with client-go interface fields\n- [ ] Implement `NewRuntimeClient(config *rest.Config) (*RuntimeClient, error)`\n- [ ] Implement `GetAgentRuntime(ctx, namespace, name)` using runtimev1alpha1 client\n- [ ] Implement `GetCodeInterpreter(ctx, namespace, name)` using runtimev1alpha1 client\n- [ ] Implement `WatchAgentRuntimes(ctx, namespace)` returning watch.Interface\n- [ ] Implement `WatchCodeInterpreters(ctx, namespace)` returning watch.Interface\n- [ ] Implement `ResolveRuntime(ctx, ref RuntimeReference)` returning RuntimeConfig\n- [ ] Add error mapping from K8s API errors to session errors\n- [ ] Write unit tests with fake client:\n  - Get existing AgentRuntime\n  - Get non-existent resource\n  - Watch operations\n  - Error mapping\n\n**Verification Command:**\n```bash\ngo test ./pkg/router/... -v -run \"TestRuntimeClient\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 11: Create Session Lifecycle Manager\n**Verifiable Output:** `pkg/router/session_lifecycle.go` with background maintenance\n\n- [ ] Create `session_lifecycle.go` file\n- [ ] Implement `StartLifecycleManager(stopCh)`:\n  - Start cleanup ticker with CleanupInterval\n  - Listen for stop signal\n- [ ] Implement `cleanupExpiredSessions(ctx)`:\n  - Call store.ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, time.Now(), batchSize)\n  - For each expired sandbox, call Terminate()\n  - Record metrics for expired sessions\n  - Log errors but continue processing\n- [ ] Implement `cleanupInactiveSessions(ctx)` (optional enhancement):\n  - Identify sessions with LastActivity > ActivityTimeout\n  - Mark for expiration or terminate\n- [ ] Write unit tests:\n  - Lifecycle manager starts and stops correctly\n  - Expired sessions are cleaned up\n  - Cleanup errors are handled gracefully\n\n**Verification Command:**\n```bash\ngo test ./pkg/router/... -v -run \"TestLifecycleManager\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 12: Create Session Metrics\n**Verifiable Output:** `pkg/router/session_metrics.go` with Prometheus metrics\n\n- [ ] Create `session_metrics.go` file\n- [ ] Define Prometheus metrics:\n  - `agentcube_session_creations_total` (CounterVec with labels: kind, result)\n  - `agentcube_active_sessions` (Gauge)\n  - `agentcube_sessions_expired_total` (Counter)\n  - `agentcube_session_resolve_duration_seconds` (HistogramVec with labels: cache_hit)\n  - `agentcube_session_duration_seconds` (Histogram)\n  - `agentcube_affinity_route_hits_total` (CounterVec with labels: result)\n- [ ] Implement `sessionMetrics` struct with all metric collectors\n- [ ] Implement `NewSessionMetrics() *sessionMetrics`\n- [ ] Implement recording methods for each metric\n- [ ] Implement `RegisterMetrics(reg prometheus.Registerer)`\n- [ ] Write unit tests verifying metrics registration\n\n**Verification Command:**\n```bash\ngo test ./pkg/router/... -v -run \"TestSessionMetrics\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 13: Implement JWT Manager\n**Verifiable Output:** `pkg/router/jwt.go` with RSA-signed JWT generation\n\n- [ ] Review and extend existing `jwt.go` if present, or create new\n- [ ] Define `JWTManager` struct with privateKey, publicKey, clientset fields\n- [ ] Implement `NewJWTManager() (*JWTManager, error)`\n- [ ] Implement `GenerateToken(claims map[string]interface{}) (string, error)`:\n  - Include standard claims: exp, iat, iss=\"agentcube-router\"\n  - Sign with RSA private key\n- [ ] Implement `TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret(ctx)`:\n  - Check for existing Secret `picod-router-identity`\n  - If not exists, generate RSA key pair\n  - Store keys in Kubernetes Secret\n  - Load keys from Secret if exists\n- [ ] Implement `ValidateToken(token string) (map[string]interface{}, error)`\n- [ ] Write unit tests:\n  - Token generation with session claims\n  - Token validation\n  - Expiration enforcement\n  - Secret storage and retrieval\n\n**Verification Command:**\n```bash\ngo test ./pkg/router/... -v -run \"TestJWTManager\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 14: Create HTTP Handlers for Session Management\n**Verifiable Output:** `pkg/router/handlers.go` with session-aware HTTP handlers\n\n- [ ] Review existing handlers from AR-009\n- [ ] Add session resolution middleware:\n  - Extract `x-agentcube-session-id` header\n  - Call SessionManager.Resolve()\n  - Store session info in context\n- [ ] Implement session injection in response headers\n- [ ] Add error handling middleware mapping session errors to HTTP status:\n  - ErrSessionNotFound → 404\n  - ErrSessionExpired → 401\n  - ErrRuntimeNotFound → 404\n  - ErrSessionStoreUnavailable → 503\n- [ ] Update proxy handler to use session affinity\n- [ ] Write unit tests:\n  - Session header extraction\n  - Error mapping to HTTP status\n  - Middleware chain functionality\n\n**Verification Command:**\n```bash\ngo test ./pkg/router/... -v -run \"TestHandlers\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 15: Integrate Session Manager with Server\n**Verifiable Output:** `pkg/router/server.go` integrates all session components\n\n- [ ] Review existing Server struct from AR-009\n- [ ] Add fields to Server struct:\n  - `sessionManager SessionManager`\n  - `jwtManager *JWTManager`\n- [ ] Update `NewServer(config)` to initialize session components\n- [ ] Add session store client initialization\n- [ ] Add K8s client initialization using client-go\n- [ ] Wire up lifecycle manager with server lifecycle\n- [ ] Register session metrics with Prometheus\n- [ ] Write unit tests for server initialization\n\n**Verification Command:**\n```bash\ngo test ./pkg/router/... -v -run \"TestServerSessionIntegration\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 16: Session Manager Full Unit Test Coverage\n**Verifiable Output:** Comprehensive unit tests for SessionManager\n\n- [ ] Create `session_manager_test.go`\n- [ ] Test `Resolve()` scenarios:\n  - Existing active session\n  - Create new session on empty ID\n  - K8s fallback on cache miss\n  - Error on resource not found\n  - Expired session handling\n- [ ] Test `Create()` scenarios:\n  - Successful creation with AgentRuntime\n  - Successful creation with CodeInterpreter\n  - Workload Manager failure\n  - Store failure\n- [ ] Test `Refresh()` scenarios:\n  - Successful refresh extends expiration\n  - Expired session returns error\n  - Missing session returns error\n- [ ] Test `Terminate()` scenarios:\n  - Successful termination\n  - Cleanup on partial failure\n- [ ] Test `ListActive()` with various filters\n- [ ] Achieve >= 80% coverage for SessionManager\n\n**Verification Command:**\n```bash\ngo test ./pkg/router/... -race -v -coverprofile=coverage.out -run \"TestSessionManager\"\ngo tool cover -func=coverage.out | grep session_manager.go\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 17: Session Resolver Unit Test Coverage\n**Verifiable Output:** Comprehensive tests for SessionResolver\n\n- [ ] Create `session_resolver_test.go`\n- [ ] Test `GetSandboxBySession()` scenarios:\n  - Cache hit returns immediately\n  - Cache miss queries K8s\n  - K8s miss returns error\n  - Successful K8s query caches result\n- [ ] Test `WarmCache()`:\n  - Preloads sessions for namespace\n  - Handles errors gracefully\n- [ ] Test concurrent resolution safety\n- [ ] Achieve >= 80% coverage for SessionResolver\n\n**Verification Command:**\n```bash\ngo test ./pkg/router/... -race -v -coverprofile=coverage.out -run \"TestSessionResolver\"\ngo tool cover -func=coverage.out | grep session_resolver.go\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 18: Affinity Router Unit Test Coverage\n**Verifiable Output:** Comprehensive tests for AffinityRouter\n\n- [ ] Create `session_affinity_test.go`\n- [ ] Test scenarios:\n  - RegisterSession adds to index\n  - GetEndpoint returns correct endpoint\n  - GetEndpoint updates LastUsed\n  - UnregisterSession removes from index\n  - HealthCheck updates status\n  - Non-existent session returns not found\n- [ ] Test concurrent operations:\n  - Multiple goroutines registering\n  - Multiple goroutines reading\n  - No race conditions (use -race flag)\n- [ ] Achieve >= 80% coverage for AffinityRouter\n\n**Verification Command:**\n```bash\ngo test ./pkg/router/... -race -v -coverprofile=coverage.out -run \"TestAffinityRouter\"\ngo tool cover -func=coverage.out | grep session_affinity.go\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 19: Integration Test - Session Lifecycle\n**Verifiable Output:** End-to-end session lifecycle works correctly\n\n- [ ] Create integration test file (build-tagged)\n- [ ] Test full session lifecycle:\n  - Create session for AgentRuntime\n  - Verify session stored correctly\n  - Resolve session returns correct info\n  - Refresh extends expiration\n  - Terminate cleans up session\n  - Verify session removed from store\n- [ ] Test session expiration:\n  - Create session with short TTL\n  - Wait for expiration\n  - Verify lifecycle manager cleans up\n- [ ] Run with `-tags=integration`\n\n**Verification Command:**\n```bash\ngo test ./pkg/router/... -v -race -run \"TestSessionLifecycle\" -tags=integration\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 20: Integration Test - Session Resolution with K8s Fallback\n**Verifiable Output:** Store miss + K8s fallback flow works\n\n- [ ] Create integration test for resolution flow:\n  - Create K8s AgentRuntime resource\n  - Query with session ID not in store\n  - Verify K8s lookup occurs\n  - Verify session created from K8s data\n  - Verify subsequent queries hit cache\n- [ ] Test Workload Manager unavailable scenario\n- [ ] Run with `-tags=integration`\n\n**Verification Command:**\n```bash\ngo test ./pkg/router/... -v -run \"TestSessionResolutionFallback\" -tags=integration\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 21: Integration Test - Session Affinity Routing\n**Verifiable Output:** Sticky routing works end-to-end\n\n- [ ] Create integration test:\n  - Register session with endpoint\n  - Multiple requests to same session ID\n  - Verify all routed to same endpoint\n  - Verify LastUsed updated\n  - Unregister and verify 404\n- [ ] Test health check integration\n- [ ] Run with `-tags=integration`\n\n**Verification Command:**\n```bash\ngo test ./pkg/router/... -v -race -run \"TestAffinityRouting\" -tags=integration\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 22: Verify JWT Token Generation and Validation\n**Verifiable Output:** JWT tokens work correctly with K8s Secret storage\n\n- [ ] Create integration test:\n  - Initialize JWTManager\n  - Verify TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret creates Secret\n  - Generate token with session claims\n  - Verify token contains correct claims\n  - Validate token succeeds\n  - Verify expired token fails validation\n- [ ] Test Secret retrieval on restart\n- [ ] Run with `-tags=integration`\n\n**Verification Command:**\n```bash\ngo test ./pkg/router/... -v -run \"TestJWTIntegration\" -tags=integration\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 23: Verify Error Handling and HTTP Mapping\n**Verifiable Output:** Session errors map correctly to HTTP responses\n\n- [ ] Create integration test:\n  - Request with invalid session ID → 400\n  - Request with non-existent session → 404\n  - Request with expired session → 401\n  - Store unavailable → 503\n- [ ] Verify response body contains correct error codes\n- [ ] Run with `-tags=integration`\n\n**Verification Command:**\n```bash\ngo test ./pkg/router/... -v -run \"TestErrorHandlingHTTP\" -tags=integration\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 24: Verify Metrics Exposure\n**Verifiable Output:** Prometheus metrics are correctly exposed\n\n- [ ] Verify all metrics are registered:\n  - agentcube_session_creations_total\n  - agentcube_active_sessions\n  - agentcube_sessions_expired_total\n  - agentcube_session_resolve_duration_seconds\n  - agentcube_session_duration_seconds\n  - agentcube_affinity_route_hits_total\n- [ ] Test metrics endpoint returns data\n- [ ] Verify metric labels are correct\n- [ ] Test metric values after operations\n\n**Verification Command:**\n```bash\ngo test ./pkg/router/... -v -run \"TestMetricsExposure\" -tags=integration\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 25: Verify Compatibility with AR-003 Client-Go\n**Verifiable Output:** Session manager works with generated client-go\n\n- [ ] Verify RuntimeClient uses correct imports from AR-003\n- [ ] Verify AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter types are accessible\n- [ ] Verify Watch interfaces work correctly\n- [ ] Check for any type incompatibilities\n\n**Verification Command:**\n```bas